data.content:
The root cause is that .NET 10's `Microsoft.AspNetCore.OpenApi` upgraded from **Microsoft.OpenApi v1.x to v2.x**, which has several breaking changes. Here's what changed and the fixes:

---

**1. `OpenApiString` / `IOpenApiAny` removed** — Examples are now `System.Text.Json.Nodes.JsonNode`:

```csharp
// Before (v1)
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Any;
param.Schema.Example = new OpenApiString("1.0");

// After (v2)
using System.Text.Json.Nodes;
param.Schema.Example = JsonValue.Create("1.0");
```

---

**2. `schema.Nullable` removed** — JSON Schema 2020-12 uses a flags enum on `Type`:

```csharp
// Before (v1)
property.Value.Nullable = false;

// After (v2) — remove the Null flag from the type
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Models;
property.Value.Type &= ~JsonSchemaType.Null;
```

To *set* nullable: `schema.Type |= JsonSchemaType.Null;`

---

**3. `ReferenceType` enum values renamed** — e.g. `SecurityScheme` → `SecurityScheme` is now under a new namespace/casing:

```csharp
// Before (v1)
Reference = new OpenApiReference { Type = ReferenceType.SecurityScheme, Id = "oauth2" }

// After (v2)
Reference = new OpenApiReference { Type = ReferenceType.SecurityScheme, Id = "oauth2" }
```

This one actually kept the same name, but you need to drop the `using Microsoft.OpenApi.Any;` import (it no longer exists) and ensure you have `using Microsoft.OpenApi.Models;`.

---

**4. `OpenApiSecurityRequirement` is no longer a `Dictionary`** — the indexer syntax changes:

```csharp
// Before (v1)
operation.Security = new List<OpenApiSecurityRequirement>
{
    new() { [oAuthScheme] = scopes }
};

// After (v2) — use the Schemes dictionary property
operation.Security = new List<OpenApiSecurityRequirement>
{
    new() { Schemes = { [oAuthScheme] = scopes } }
};
```

---

### Full corrected code

```csharp
using System.Text.Json.Nodes;          // replaces Microsoft.OpenApi.Any
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Models;

options.AddOperationTransformer((operation, context, ct) =>
{
    var param = operation.Parameters.FirstOrDefault(p => p.Name == "api-version");
    if (param is not null)
    {
        param.Schema.Example = JsonValue.Create("1.0");       // JsonNode
    }

    operation.Responses.TryAdd("401", new OpenApiResponse { Description = "Unauthorized" });

    var oAuthScheme = new OpenApiSecurityScheme
    {
        Reference = new OpenApiReference { Type = ReferenceType.SecurityScheme, Id = "oauth2" }
    };
    operation.Security = new List<OpenApiSecurityRequirement>
    {
        new() { Schemes = { [oAuthScheme] = scopes } }        // Schemes property
    };

    return Task.CompletedTask;
});

options.AddSchemaTransformer((schema, context, ct) =>
{
    if (schema.Properties is not null)
    {
        foreach (var property in schema.Properties)
        {
            if (schema.Required?.Contains(property.Key) != true)
                property.Value.Type &= ~JsonSchemaType.Null;  // replaces Nullable
        }
    }
    return Task.CompletedTask;
});
```

**Summary of removals:**
| v1 (OpenApi 1.x) | v2 (OpenApi 2.x) |
|---|---|
| `Microsoft.OpenApi.Any` namespace | Removed — use `System.Text.Json.Nodes` |
| `new OpenApiString("x")` | `JsonValue.Create("x")` |
| `schema.Nullable = bool` | `schema.Type \|= / &= ~JsonSchemaType.Null` |
| `new() { [scheme] = scopes }` | `new() { Schemes = { [scheme] = scopes } }` |
